topogram

Antoine Bichat

25/08/2020

topogram permet de crer des cartogrammes, cest dire des cartes pour lesquelle la surface des territoires reprsents est proportionnelle une variable.

Nous allons reprsenter le nombre des victimes du coronavirus par pays.

# remotes::install_github("RamiKrispin/coronavirus")
library(coronavirus)
library(tidyverse)

On rcupre et met en forme le jeu de donne des cas de coronavirus au 2020-08-25.

df_covid <-
  coronavirus %>%
  filter(type == "death") %>%
  group_by(country) %>%
  summarise(total_death = sum(cases), .groups = "drop") %>% # sommer les morts journaliers
  mutate(country = case_when(country == "US" ~ "United States", # pour le left_join()
                             country == "Congo (Kinshasa)" ~ "Dem. Rep. Congo",
                             country == "Congo (Brazzaville)" ~ "Congo",
                             country == "Cote d'Ivoire" ~ "Cte d'Ivoire",
                             country == "Central African Republic" ~ "Central African Rep.",
                             country == "Taiwan*" ~ "Taiwan",
                             country == "Equatorial Guinea" ~ "Eq. Guinea",
                             country == "South Sudan" ~ "S. Sudan",
                             country == "Western Sahara" ~ "W. Sahara",
                             country == "Korea, South" ~ "Korea",
                             country == "Czechia" ~ "Czech Rep.",
                             country == "Laos" ~ "Lao PDR",
                             country == "Bosnia and Herzegovina" ~ "Bosnia and Herz.",
                             TRUE    ~ country), # il reste d'autres inadquations dans les noms
         total_death = total_death + 1) # pour viter les 0
df_covid

On rcupre la carte du monde et on la fusionne le jeu de donnes du coronavirus.

# install.packages("rnaturalearth")
# remotes::install_github("dreamRs/topogram")
# remotes::install_github("ropensci/rnaturalearthhires")
library(rnaturalearth)
library(coronavirus)
library(topogram)
library(sf)
## Linking to GEOS 3.7.2, GDAL 2.4.2, PROJ 5.2.0
world_covid <- 
  countries110 %>% 
  st_as_sf() %>% 
  left_join(df_covid, by = c("name" = "country")) %>% 
  drop_na(total_death) %>% 
  select(name, total_death)

La fontion topogram fait le travail.

topogram(shape = world_covid,
         value = "total_death",
         tooltip_label = ~ name,
         n_iteration = 100,
         unit_value = "deaths",
         format_value = ".2s") %>% # D3 format for two significant digits
  add_labs(title = "Number of death by Covid-19") %>%
  add_legend(title = "", orientation = "vertical",
             label_format = ".2s")
